Cyfrowy Polsat of Poland Completes Purchase of Telewizja Polsat

-- B y   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 
2011-04-21T16:47:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/cyfrowy-polsat-of-poland-completes-purchase-of-telewizja-polsat.html
Cyfrowy Polsat SA (CPS) , Polandâ€™s biggest
satellite television broadcaster, completed the purchase of
Telewizja Polsat SA, controlled by billionaire Zygmunt Solorz-
Zak, for 3.75 billion zloty ($1.4 billion).  Cyfrowy will pay 2.6 billion zloty within 48 days and the
rest has already been paid in the form of shares, the Warsaw-
based company said in a regulatory statement today. Following
the deal, Cyfrowy plans to pay no dividend from 2010 net income,
the company said in a separate statement today.  The new entity will become the biggest Polish media
company, Cyfrowy Polsat said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
